name: Fila 96 “Bulls By The Horns”
description: There will be another FILA 96 offering on store shelves next week, as the sneaker is readying itself for the release of the “Bulls by the Horns” pack. That means a very Chicago-esque colorway featuring black patent leather for the piping along with some minimal hits of red down in the accents. Its brethren from the pack end up a little heavier on the black and red, with this Grant Hill classic opting to go too terribly far into that territory.

name: Fila ’96 “Tradition Pack”
description: Fila’s nostalgia inducing “Tradition Pack” is just a few days away. Amongst the OG offerings included in the crop is this, a Fila ’96 (Remember that’s the Grant Hill II) that Grant brought along with him for the 1996 NBA All-Star Game. Of course he wore them on and off throughout the season that year, but we’re assuming you’d best remember them from that performance. The shoes sport the same red, white, and blue style combo sprinkled throughout the collection.
